The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Arcelor net income up
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Arcelor net income up
                            
	London, Aug. 11 (PTI): ArcelorMittal has reported a 48.91 per cent rise in net income at $8.80 billion, including minority interest, for the six months ended June 30 over the corresponding period a year ago. The firm had a net income of $5.91 billion during the same period in 2007, ArcelorMittal said in a statement.        
	The worlds largest steel maker registered sales of $67.65 billion for the reporting period, a 31 per cent jump compared with $51.70 billion a year ago.        
	During the period under review, ArcelorMittal repurchased about 22.6 million shares under its 44 million share buyback programme, at an average of $75.97 per share.        
	The company also completed its $1-billion share buy-back programme with the purchase of 14.6 million shares.                                                                                                                                      
